JOHANNESBURG - Police have confirmed an investigation into a fatal accident on the M1 south which involved two suspected hijackers on Sunday morning.READ: Four dead in horrific Joburg car crashAccording to police spokesperson Captain Mavela Masondo the suspects, in an attempt to escape police pursuit, drove into oncoming traffic on the M1 south and collided with another vehicle instantly killing both suspects and two people in the oncoming vehicle.READ: Two suspected hijackers among deceased in M1 collision Four people died in this incident. The two suspects and two people in another car. The suspects vehicle was also found to have been hijacked in Johannesburg on Saturday. Cases of culpable homicide, reckless and negligent driving and possession of a hijacked vehicle have been opened and investigations are underway. Added Masondo.eNCA